AWS VPC â€” The Heart of Cloud Networking (Explained Simply)
 
In AWS, a VPC (Virtual Private Cloud) is your own private, isolated, and secure network where you host applications, databases, and microservices.
 
Every DevOps, DevSecOps, and Cloud Engineer must understand VPC because it is the foundation of all cloud architectures.

